A hotel De Lankaster Hotel  located in the highbrow area of Lekki has been blacklisted by Nigerians after an alleged rape incident took place at the hotel. Read More: Nigerians Allege Linda Ikeji Was Paid To Take Down Rape Story <img class="size-full wp-image-852161 aligncenter lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/de-lankaster-hotel-and-suites-lagos-69265.jpg" alt="" width="1160" height="507" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/de-lankaster-hotel-and-suites-lagos-69265.jpg 1160w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/de-lankaster-hotel-and-suites-lagos-69265-1062x464.jpg 1062w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/de-lankaster-hotel-and-suites-lagos-69265-487x213.jpg 487w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/de-lankaster-hotel-and-suites-lagos-69265-974x426.jpg 974w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/de-lankaster-hotel-and-suites-lagos-69265-320x140.jpg 320w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/de-lankaster-hotel-and-suites-lagos-69265-640x280.jpg 640w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/de-lankaster-hotel-and-suites-lagos-69265-600x262.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1160px) 100vw, 1160px" /> According to reports, two men, Don Chima George and Razak Segun had taken a 23-year-old girl to one of De Lankaster’s rooms (owned by Don Chima’s father) got her drugged, raped and filmed the assault. Less than 24 hours after the two culprits were arrested, they were released. Since the news broke, the hotel which had a 4.7-star rating has dropped to 1.3% and threatens to go down further. At the time of this report, 237 reviews have been written: See some of the reviews below: <img class="aligncenter wp-image-852154 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Review-1.png" alt="" width="1280" height="1038" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Review-1.png 555w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Review-1-487x395.png 487w,https://gu